# NEVER Use MapFallbackToFile

## Prohibition

**NEVER add `MapFallbackToFile`, `MapFallback`, or any SPA-style catch-all fallback** to this application.

This is a **multi-page application** with separate HTML files. It is **NOT** a Single-Page Application (SPA). There is no client-side router.

## Why This Exists

`MapFallbackToFile("index.html")` prevents IIS from issuing its built-in trailing-slash redirect on virtual application roots (`/ServerMonitorDashboard` → `/ServerMonitorDashboard/`). Without the redirect, the browser URL lacks a trailing slash and every relative CSS/JS path resolves to the wrong location, breaking all styling.

## Correct Static File Configuration

```csharp
app.UseDefaultFiles();    // Rewrites / → /index.html
app.UseStaticFiles();     // Serves wwwroot/* files
// No fallback. No catch-all.
```
